Basic Structure of C Language:
------------------------
1:Documentation Section:
Comments : Comments are those lines that is not executable by compiler.
   i):Single Line Comment:  //
   ii):Multiline Comment  /*...text..*/
----------------------------------------   
2:Linking section:
    header files:Header files are the collection of pre-defined function.
	Whenever you need those functions in your program firstly you have to include the header 
	files in the program.
	----------------------
	#->It is pre-processor Directive
	include->folder name
	stdio->header file
	----------------------
	#include<stdio.h>
	#include<conio.h>
	#include<String.h>
---------------------------------------
3:Global Declaration Section:

---------------------------------------
4;Main Function:
main()//It is pre-defined function
{
   //body of main function or block of main function
}
---------------------------------------
